One person was said to have died in an accident involving a Dangote cement truck and a Bajaj motorcycle in Ogun State. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) confirmed this incident in a statement on Friday. The Ogun FRSC Spokesperson, Florence Okpe, said the crash occurred at about 0930HRS on Mosinmi-Sagamu route, around Meriton Company. Okpe disclosed that four persons – three men and one woman – were involved in the accident. While one man died in the road crash, the three others were rescued unhurt. “The suspected cause of the crash was wrongful overtaking,” the FRSC confirmed. The corpse, it was said, had been deposited at the Olabisi Onabanjo Teaching Hospital, Sagamu.